IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
On 4/11/2023 at approximately 1530 hours, M/Tpr. Hood was instructed to respond to the FedEx Ground Facility located in Hagerstown Maryland for a parcel containing suspected CDS. Upon arrival M/Tpr. Hood made contact with FedEx personnel regarding the parcel. M/Tpr. Hood was given two parcels coming from California to Silver Spring Maryland. Both parcels were opened, and the contents inside were falling out. Both parcels contained a plastic bin with what looked to be suspected kilos of CDS. M/Tpr. Hood confirmed one of the parcels contained five (5) kilos and the other contained six (6) kilos. The parcels were then signed over to M/Tpr. Hood and transported to the Hagerstown State Police Barracks. On 4/12/2023 M/Tpr. Hood transported the two parcels to the Maryland State Police Crime Lab for testing. Each kilogram was weighed, and a sample was taken from each parcel. The preliminary test determined that the white powdery substance was in fact cocaine. Both parcels were then placed on MSP evidence via PH# 343913 and MSP form 67. Notification was made, to Cpl. Deibel, however due to FedEx opening the parcels prior to contacting M/Tpr. Hood there was no attempt made for a controlled delivery. The property will be stored at the Hagerstown State Police Barracks for further investigation.

All the above events occurred in Washington County Maryland.
